description: The Morgendorffers move to Lawndale, where Quinn becomes a member of the Fashion Club and Daria meets an equally cynical artist named Jane during a self-esteem class taught by their neurotic, wimpy English teacher, Mr. O'Neill.
name: Esteemsters

description: To Quinn's horror, Daria is invited to Brittany's party after helping her solve an art class problem, and Jane tags along.
name: The Invitation

description: The Morgendorffers visit Middleton College - Jake and Helen's alma mater, where Quinn goes to a frat party and Daria finds brisk business writing term papers.
name: College Bored

description: The students of Lawndale High raise money selling objects door-to-door to raise money for a new café after the old one is burglarized.
name: Cafe Disaffecto

description: A modeling agency comes to Lawndale High to recruit female students, and end up picking Quinn as one of the candidates, before zeroing in on stupid Lawndale High QB Kevin Thompson.
name: This Year's Model

description: For a class project for the man-hating science teacher, Ms. Barch, Daria is paired with jock Kevin, while Brittany works with resident pervert, Charles "Upchuck" Ruttenheimer.
name: The Lab Brat

description: Quinn is chosen to babysit for an ultra-conservative family's children, but Daria steps in when Quinn has a date.
name: Pinch  Sitter

deck: Wonder Woman battles an Irish terrorist that has a formula for causing earthquakes and who plans to use it on Washington D.C.
name: The Pluto File

description: Quinn is afraid she's not cute enough and wants plastic surgery after seeing a fellow classmate with a nose job. Meanwhile, Kevin is chosen by Ms. Barch to disguise himself as an ugly man and chart people's reactions.
name: Too Cute

description: After getting caught sneaking in the house past curfew, Helen and Jake set up "Family Court" and sentence Daria and Quinn to being grounded.
name: The Big House

deck: There is a Nazi plot to flood the USA with counterfeit money.  Wonder Woman and Steve work together to foil it.
name: The Last of the Two Dollar Bills

description: Daria travels with Jane, Jane's brother, Trent, and Trent's friend, Jessie (both make up half of Mystik Spiral), to Alternapalooza while Quinn begins her travels there with her Fashion Club friends.
name: Road Worrier

description: The Morgendorffers go camping after Jake suffers a burst blood vessel in his eye due to stress over money. Meanwhile, Jane and Trent try to survive a hostile family reunion.
name: The Teachings of Don Jake

deck: The Intergalactic Council sends a delegate to Earth to gain information on the Second World War and whether Earth should be destroyed instead of letting it destroy itself.  The delegate is first thought to be a spy, but is later captured by the Germans.  The Intergalactic Council decrees that if anything happens to the delegate that Earth will be destroyed.  Wonder Woman and Steve rush to rescue him.
name: Judgment from Outer Space Part 1

deck: Wonder Woman and Steve save Andros the alien from the Germans
name: Judgment from Outer Space Part 2

deck: Wonder Woman and Steve Trevor obtain a formula to create super strong rubber while in Argentina.  They are kidnapped by the Germans and must escape.
name: Formula 407

deck: Nazi cattle rustlers in Texas must be stopped.
description: This episode featured a costume change for Wonder Woman to reflect the Western setting
name: The Bushwackers

deck: A nazi agent posing as a film producer kidnaps a number of soldiers (including Steve) in order to take them to Germany to create an a propaganda film.  Wonder Woman must rescue them with the help of Wonder Girl.
name: Wonder Woman in Hollywood
That Was Then, This is Dumb

deck: The first appearance of Beavis & Butt-Head
description: The infamous first appearance of Beavis and Butt-Head, which originally aired on MTV's Liquid Television with no music videos. Videos were added after the episode aired among the other shorts in the Beavis & Butt-Head series. The episode is often held up by critics of the show as being immature and violent, before it was acknowledged as parody of a youth culture in the 1990s.
name: Frog Baseball

deck: Two becomes three, as Oolong joins Goku & Bulma in their search for the Dragon Balls. Next, their quest brings them to the unforgiving depths of the scorching Diablo Dessert, and beyond it, another Dragon Ball lies in wait! But their trek will not be an easy one; the desert is home to the infamous Yamcha the Bandit!
description:
Original Title: つよくて悪い砂漠のヤムチャ (Tsuyokote Warui Sabaku no Yamucha)

The episode begins with the trio sailing down river on a boat. It doesn't take long for Oolong to instigate the first of many escape attempts. He transforms into a fish and tries to flee by swimming but is swiftly recaptured by Bulma's rather special 'lure.' After this failed bid, Bulma offers Oolong a piece of 'candy' but denies Goku some. When they reach the shore, Bulma, to her horror, finds that she has mislaid her DynoCaps. Oolong attempts to flee again, but Bulma yells "Piggy!," a cue which causes Oolong to have bowel movements so severe he needs to go to the toilet. His future obedience all but ensured.

Later on, the gang is seen pacing across the unforgiving Diablo Desert, unknowingly being observed from afar. Bulma, unable to hack the heat any longer decides to take a rest and lies down in the shade, leaving Goku & Oolong to talk amongst themselves. But, before long, the gang is greeted by a man and blue feline duo of Yamcha & Pu'ar. Almost straight away Oolong recognizes the blue feline as Pu'ar, and immediately starts taunting him, while Yamcha, desiring to lighten the gang of their goods, starts a fight with Goku.

During the exchange, Yamcha unleashes his fierce some technique, the Wolf Fang Fist" sending Goku flying backwards to collide with a mound of rock. Eventually, the fight is brought to a close when Bulma wakes up and rises to, looking around the place. Yamcha instantly spots her, and almost as quickly his face flushes scarlet as his weakness paralyses him; Yamcha is deathly afraid of Woman!

Before the pair make for a hasty exit, Bulma catches a glimpse of Yamcha and is immediately star stuck, while back at home base, Yamcha vows future vengeance on Goku.
name: Yamcha the Desert Bandit

deck: The search resumes for the elusive Dragon Balls, with the next stop being the quiet Aru Village. However, once arriving there Goku & Bulma seem to think the place has been abandoned. But, soon they learn of a evil monster who can change his form at will has been raising hell in the village. Goku & Bulma agree to help rid the villagers of the monster, in exchange for receiving a Dragon Ball of course!
description:
Original Title: 人さらい妖怪ウーロン (Hitosarai Youkai Uuron)

Goku & Bulma travel ever further on their quest to unite the seven Dragon Balls. Their next port of call is Aru Village, which Goku decides to investigate for traces of another Dragon Ball. As the two enter the village, Bulma remarks that the settlement resembles a ghost town, and idly ponders where all the residents are, and more important still, what is causing them to behave in such a reclusive manner.

Goku breaks into one of the houses -- only to receive an axe smashing against his skull for his efforts. The tool effortlessly shatters, however, and while Goku ruminants on the alarming action, a shocked Shaman goes on to explain the situation. It seems that a nasty, shape-shifting monster called Oolong has been giving the locals all kinds of grief, accumulating in the abduction of young village girls. The shaman goes on to say that his daughter is the next one to get picked by the monster.

Then, after not perceiving any danger the villagers begin to gather outside the shaman's house. Bulma uses this chance to ask the shaman if he has any Dragon Balls in his possess, and takes out one of them to give him an example. The shaman admits he hasn't, but Bulma receives a response from a voice in the crowd. An old woman proposes that she will be willing to part ways with the lustrous marble in exchange for them helping to get rid of Oolong.

They both accept, and so Bulma concocts a canny scheme to trap Oolong in. Unfortunately, her plan soon goes up in smoke, but they eventually succeed in ridding the village of the not-so-scary monster, and also gain a new companion in the process.
name: Oolong the Terrible

description:
Sex Education is a special time in every young person's life, in which they learn about the facts of life. For Highland High's Coach Buzzcut, it's an endurance test, for he must constantly deal with the tittering laughter of students Beavis and Butt-Head without committing homicide. However, this year, the boys go too far, and a punishment from Principal McVicker ensures that, one way or another, Buzzcut will get some peace of mind. Will our zero heroes make it through sex ed. week intact?

Beavis & Butt-Head watch videos from Ween, Carmen Electra, Butthole Surfers, Beastie Boys, Amy Grant, Toni Basil, the Scorpions, Reba McIntire, Duran Duran, and Corrosion of Conformity.
name: No Laughing

description:
Plot Summary

As the vampire craze hits Beavis and Butt-Head's high school, the two try to join the broody undead to score chicks. But when they confuse a hirsute homeless man for a werewolf, it's a case of once bitten, twice infected with Hep-C.
name: Werewoles of Highland

description:
Plot Summary

The wusses in old movies teach the boys that scoring with a chick may be as simple as asking her father for her hand. Do they have any idea what they're getting into? Or are they just looking for a handout?
name: Daughter's Hand

description:
Plot Summary

Just do IT: When Beavis and Butt-Head are accidentally hired as Tech Support geeks, will they end up crashing the system for good? Looks like Co Tech outsourced to the wrong dudes. Will their cubicle mate Hamid be able to help, or will he fall victim to their perverted pranks?
name: Tech Support

description:
Plot Summary

Butt-Head is really screwed when a visit to the hospital once again awakens The Great Cornoholio in Beavis. But two rooms over, the leader of a cult has died. Is the Great Cornholio destined to be the cult's idiot savior? Cornholio's hopped up babble certainly sounds holy, and the idiot worship begins. Soon they're promised to be with their pick of the ladies. Will they mess this one up? You bet your bunghole!
name: Holy Cornholio

description:
Plot Summary

At ease, gentlemen! When Van Driessen takes the class on a field trip to a military base, it's Beavis and Butt-Head in the virtual pilot seats of drone planes on a Middle Eastern mission. They feel the need for speed, but is it a video game or real life? When these two are in the hot seat, it's only a matter of time before the general has their head! (Huh-huh, he said 'head.')
name: Drones

description:
Plot Summary

Beavis is no wuss, but get him near onions and he can't keep a tear from falling. Too bad for Beavis, because when Butt-Head catches him crying, he'll never hear the end of it!
name: Crying

description:
Plot Summary

Everyone gets blown out of proportion when Beavis and Butt-Head make a documentary about teen obesity to score chicks. Will super-sizing themselves get them fame, fortune and fine females? Or are they finally too big for their britches?
name: Supersize Me

description:
Plot Summary

When Butt-Head realizes that he and Beavis get paid even when they're using the bathroom, things at Burger World go to pot. Their manager doesn't like it, but a labor lawyer puts the power in their dumbass hands. With labor laws on their side, there's nothing these idiots won't avoid.
name: Bathroom Break

description:
Plot Summary

A fool and his nachos are soon parted... by a rat? When a rat takes up residence in Beavis and Butt-head's kitchen, they'll stop at nothing until the kitchen at Burger World has one too.
name: The Rat

description:
Plot Summary

Filthy chicks at the beach! An oil spills draws hot hippies to the shoreline, and Beavis and Butt-head try to get eco-friendly with these granola girls. But when all the 'filthy chicks' are taking wing, will the boys see the value of dirty work, or are they just too crude?
name: Spill

description:
Plot Summary

It's the end of the world as they know it, and Beavis and Butt-head feel fine. When the apocalypse leaves them behind, Highland's biggest idiots have run of the town. Will they finally score? Not even when they're the last men on earth.
name: Doomsday

description:
Plot Summary

Evolution of dumbass: When a religious group encourages them to take a stand against a science lesson, these brain-dead idiots take the cue to check out. They can't get a clue, but will they get religion just to get out of class?
name: Dumb Design

description:
Plot Summary

Do you copy, your butt? It's Beavis' behind on the line when Butt-Head convinces him to duplicate his derriere on the new copier. When the glass breaks, extracting his backside could mean life or death for Beavis' butt!
name: Copy Machine

description:
Plot Summary

Boioioing! There's a whole lot of shaking going on when two porn stars confuse twitchy compadres Beavis and Butt-Head for drug dealers. Are these porn stars ready to score with these amateurs? Is this their lucky day, or is everyone going down?
name: Holding

description:
Plot Summary

No license, no money, no problem! Beavis and Butt-Head shanghai a used car salesman on a joyride that leaves the car in pieces. Will they walk away from this one, or is everything wrecked for good?
name: Used Car

description:
Plot Summary

Beavis and Butt-Head become ace bounty hunters after a chance meeting with a reality TV star in a hardware store. Will these vigilantes land a real fugitive? They soon find out catching criminals takes more than mullets and sleeveless shirts!
name: Bounty Hunters

description: Robbie is framed for robbery, and only Spider-Man and Jameson believe that he's innocent. Can they find enough evidence to prove it before Robbie meets some old "friends" in prison?
name: Partners in Danger Chapter 1: Guilty

description: Doctor Octopus and Kingpin break Felicia's father, John Hardesky aka The Cat, from prison. As a boy, The Cat witnessed the creation of Captain America and knows the formula they used. Now Kingpin wants the information for himself.
name: Partners in Danger Chapter 2: The Cat
A Very Special Christmas with Beavis and Butt-Head

description: A mysterious figure called The Black Cat appears in New York and asks for Spider-Man's help in freeing John Hardesky from the Kingpin.
name: Partners in Danger Chapter 3: The Black Cat

description: Spider-Man has been refusing to work with Black Cat because he doesn't want anyone close to him getting hurt anymore. Meanwhile, Kraven returns to New York to hunt down the Stalker, a creature he has been said to have created.
name: Partners in Danger Chapter 4: Return of Kraven

description:
After the dim-witted duo respond to a phone sex ad on television, Beavis and Butt-Head are inspired to try to get their own party line. Could this lead the industrious idiots to continuing their proud family lines? Will Beavis and Butt-Head earn the bank they need to buy the cool snake tattoos of their dreams, or at least some sour cream and salsa pork rinds? Tune in and find out.

Beavis and Butt-Head "enjoy" videos during this episode from Eve's Plum, Barry White, and Low Pop Suicide.
name: 1-900-BEAVIS

description: Smythe kidnaps Black Cat and tells Spider-Man that he'll set her free if he finds Scorpion or the Vulture. Smythe is planning to help make Silvermane an adult again using the neogenics from the two of them.
name: Partners in Danger Chapter 5: Partners

description: Debra Whitman finds Michael Morbius in hibernation, on an island off of New York City. Felicia, as Black Cat, asks for help from Blade's partner, Whistler, in finding a cure for Morbius' mutation.
name: Partners in Danger Chapter 6: The Awakening

description: Blade's mother, the Vampire Queen, has come to New York and is hoping to transformer everyone into vampires. To stop her, Blade, Black Cat, and Spider-Man will need Morbius' help.
name: Partners in Danger Chapter 7: The Vampire Queen
